It looks like this could also be a Dask Series array or anything that implements a `map_partitions` method that applies that function over iterables.  Perhaps something like the following would work instead?

```python
if hasattr(X, 'map_partitions):
    return X.map_partitions(transformer)
```

Also, what is the desired return type here?  Do we want this to be a Dask array of sparse arrays?  My guess is that dask.bag wouldn't give that to us by default

This is a pretty messy line.  I'd recommend simplifying this to:

```python
def __init__(self, ...):
  if self._should_warn_for_namespace(label_namespace):
    ...

def _should_warn_for_namespace(self, label_namespace):
  if label_namespace.endswith('labels') or label_namespace.endswith('tags'):
    if label_namespace not in self._already_warned_namespaces:
      logger.warning("...")
      self._already_warned_namespaces.add(label_namespace)
```

This has the benefit of also moving the multi-line warning statement out of the constructor, which will make this class easier to read.

I guess i was thinking

